### CloudWatch – Main Purpose

**CloudWatch monitors AWS resources and applications.**

**Interview Answer:**

> "We use AWS CloudWatch to monitor servers, applications, CPU usage, memory, disk space, logs, and application health. 
It helps us identify issues and create alerts when thresholds are exceeded."

**Simple Example:**

> "If EC2 CPU utilization goes above 80%, CloudWatch detects it and triggers an alarm."

---

### SNS – Main Purpose

**SNS sends notifications and alerts.**

**Interview Answer:**

> "We use AWS SNS to send email notifications to the DevOps team whenever CloudWatch detects an issue such as high CPU usage, server downtime, application failure, or deployment failure."

**Simple Example:**

> "When CloudWatch detects CPU usage above 80%, it triggers SNS, and SNS sends an email notification to the team."

---

### Project-Based Interview Answer

> "In our project, we used CloudWatch to monitor EC2 instances, application logs, and infrastructure metrics.
We configured CloudWatch Alarms for critical thresholds such as CPU, memory, and disk utilization. 
Whenever an alarm was triggered, CloudWatch sent notifications through SNS to the DevOps team via email, allowing us to respond quickly and minimize downtime."

---

### One-Line Interview Answer

> **CloudWatch monitors AWS resources, and SNS sends alerts to the team when CloudWatch detects issues.**



